			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of 16-year-old K. H. on the deportation of his family to Kamenets-Podolsk in the summer of 1941, hiding in
					Kőrösmező/Yasina, finding shelter in a Jewish orphans’ home in Budapest, his arrest and deportation to Auschwitz, his experiences
					in Buchenwald, the IG Farben (Brabag) synthetic fuel factory in Rehmsdorf, and his liberation in Theresienstadt.</p>
			</abstract>
